Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.45,0:01:42.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,Munakata Family Hereditary Tomb{Lit: Munakata Family Ancestors Have been living here for generation after generation - too bulky and confusing to my taste}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.00,0:01:47.56,Sign,,0,0,0,,Dear{/To Mr.} Munakata Jin.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.85,0:01:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear Jin Munakata,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.67,0:01:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how many more I will bring here.{"tsume" part is a complete guess, none of the meanings seem to make sense here, so I'm taking the middle ground between johnny's variant and the meanings I could gather}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.97,0:01:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I never pasted a stamp, \Nnor put one into the post box.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.66,0:01:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet I kept writing and hoarding{can't hear the last word, assumed it's kazu} \Nmy letters to you this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.16,0:02:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been yearning for you \Never since I was a child.{this is a problematic line, since previously I made Jin say "turns out I have a sis" as if he just met Ranko which is canonic with the plot, and since she was never shown younger than a middle-schooler, I would assume it is that period she refers to as "since I was small", however shoehorned}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.74,0:02:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, whenever I wander through my many memories, \Nyou end up appearing before me, in one form or another.{this line is very liberal but is also very lirical at the same time}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.55,0:02:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When I entered middle school,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.27,0:02:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I was disquieted by being much taller than everyone, \Nso much, I barely ever showed outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.77,0:02:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the person who coerced me to show up{/dragged me out} \Non the tennis court for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.52,0:02:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, I was obsessed with this - writing love letters \None after another, without ever handing them to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.22,0:02:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, you were also the one \Nwho brought me two raison d'être{Midorikawa often uses colloquial and unusual words/constructions, so I'm trying to reflect that wont of her here as well} in one go -
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.10,0:02:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,tennis \Nand my first love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.94,0:02:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,By that time, I have only been told \Nyou are a son of dad's ancient friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.99,0:02:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I learned the truth \Nas soon as I entered high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.78,0:02:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Though we had different mothers, \Nyou turned out to be my blood-related brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.08,0:02:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However, my feelings were already \Npast the point of no return.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.64,0:02:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Jin, did you ever tumble to{/get a notion of} my feelings?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.96,0:02:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Cos I truly... Truly...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.38,0:03:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Loved you.{/Fell in love with you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.12,0:03:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Read them all, my love letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.54,0:03:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I can finally confer them to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.49,0:03:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As for now,{it's actually another "dear" but that's a bit too much for one line} Dear Munakata Jin,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.57,0:03:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I can no longer receive a ball from you, \Ntherefore...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.41,0:03:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,My tennis is no more as well.{/It's over for my tennis as well.}
