Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.90,0:03:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunrise is magnificent here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.82,0:04:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she managed to get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.14,0:04:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she stayed up all night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.66,0:04:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Without ever touching the futon, she sat by the window, \Nlooking at the sea, though she couldn't see any.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.65,0:04:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,"What are you looking at?" \NWhen I asked her so,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.56,0:04:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord4}what do you think was this child's answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.18,0:04:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord4}"The sound of the surf{/the sea}. Time after time, \Nit's always different.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.37,0:04:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord3}It never produces{/repeats} the same sound twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.34,0:04:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that passed \Ncan never return again."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.97,0:04:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I was completely at a loss \Nas for what I should tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.26,0:04:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As parents, we can do naught \Nbut wait and look{ patiently}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.81,0:04:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's the first time for her{ to experience such a thing}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.27,0:04:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,However, what we're seeing is perhaps a beginning \Nof Hiromi's existence as an independent individual.{Lit: But perhaps, this testifies to the beginning of Hiromi's existence as an independent human being.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.02,0:04:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. It's for the times like that, \Nthat{todo: remove?} we brought Hiromi up this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.15,0:04:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She won't cave in. Not{ our} Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.82,0:04:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- Fight.\N- {\i1}Fight!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.16,0:05:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? You alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.89,0:05:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.39,0:05:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.00,0:05:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.40,0:05:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts so much you can't get up? \NLet me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.07,0:05:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you didn't even break or twist anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.32,0:05:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Please put me down! \NI'm alright, Coach! Coach...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.24,0:05:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, I'm alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.99,0:05:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Be careful next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.79,0:05:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.50,0:05:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, shall we carry on?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.89,0:05:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.67,0:05:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- Fight!\N- {\i1}Fight!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.52,0:06:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, this morning I called the hotel \Nwhere Hiromi is staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.92,0:06:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then her mother picked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.73,0:06:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi barely touches the food, \Ndoing nothing but staring at the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.65,0:06:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What an idiot Hiromi really is!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.73,0:06:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If she doesn't eat, \Nit's all over for her, Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.70,0:06:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, she's an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.35,0:06:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,She gives me nothing but worries! \NAfter this, I'm going after Hiromi too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.47,0:06:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, I beseech you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.56,0:06:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- Give me some strength...\N- Aikawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.82,0:06:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This racket... Who left it here?{/I wonder who it belongs to.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.38,0:06:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.97,0:06:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Midorikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.01,0:06:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,By discarding tennis, \Nyou can't drive away{/run away from the/forget} the sorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.14,0:06:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But as long as you keep playing tennis, \Nas long as you keep hitting that yellow{again, she says white but I take it it's some jargon at this point to miscolor the tennis ball} ball, Coach lives on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.90,0:06:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Both in our hearts \Nand in our tennis alike!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.27,0:06:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Discarding tennis like that \Nmeans discarding Coach as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.78,0:06:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to overcome it. Hiromi too, and Midorikawa too. \NAs well as the rest of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Only by overcoming this grief, \Nyou can then rise back to your feet!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.33,0:07:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It looked as though Madame Butterfly \Nis talking to herself back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.17,0:07:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think she is right.{/I think so too.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.96,0:07:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't she, Hiromi?\NHiromi, are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.34,0:07:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.39,0:07:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I would rather die!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.89,0:07:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.89,0:07:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.46,0:07:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I would rather die, Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.32,0:07:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi! Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.07,0:07:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach! Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.27,0:07:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.11,0:07:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Idiot, idiot, idiot! \N- I would rather die!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.30,0:07:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.22,0:08:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for answering my call{ [for a meeting]}.\NMy name is Daigo Katsura.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.63,0:08:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing, we are grateful to you likewise \Nfor coming all the way here to help our dear daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.57,0:08:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you excuse me, \NI'll get straight to the point.{/I'll be speaking frankly.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.90,0:08:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you entrust young lady{/your daughter} \Ninto my custody in the temple for some time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.45,0:08:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhist temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.54,0:08:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you hope to achieve?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.12,0:08:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope to relieve{/succor/rescue} the young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.91,0:08:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for detouring into my own story...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.42,0:08:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When Munakata Jin \Nreceived a first blow from his disease,{/was first attacked by the disease.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.14,0:08:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,we were in the middle of a practice match \Nfor that year's All-Japan Championship{guess - "muketu'}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.97,0:08:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.04,0:08:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Like hell!{/We'll see about that!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.44,0:08:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The exact diagnosis was not yet apparent.{Lit: It was unclear what the disease in question name is.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.78,0:08:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So we only let the barebones \N{in the form }of "seizures{/convulsions} of unknown origin" to leak out{/to be announced/published}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.48,0:09:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But his actual diagnosis was \Nmarrow leukemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.97,0:09:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a lethal disease \Nwith no chance for remission.{/no odds to be cured.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.55,0:09:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When he first learned about it after the hospitalization, \Nwith an eerie glow in his eyes, he told me this:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.48,0:09:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Daigo, I got three more years to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.33,0:09:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I was utterly shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.54,0:09:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When such fate hit my one and only best friend,\N{/When I learned of this fate, awaiting my one and only best friend, }
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.07,0:09:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,obvious emotions like grief or bitterness \Nwere just the tip of the iceberg for me.{/I was engulfed by much more than just unsophisticated emotions like sadness and heartbreak.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.85,0:09:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll die in three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.63,0:09:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, it felt like a death sentence in just three days \Nwould have been more bearable.{/In some ways, this was even more brutal than, say, having just 3 days left to live.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.59,0:09:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, for the next three years, \Nhe'll be constantly hearing the breath of death.{/staring the death in the face.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.18,0:09:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Second after second, day after day...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.29,0:09:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a thought of Munakata's next three years \Nwas agonizing to my very existence.{/was making the pain run through my body.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.37,0:09:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I began drinking heavily, \Ncursing myself for leading {such }a carefree life.{"nounou" in the beginning has a good chance of being both "carefree life" and "heavy drinking and life" so I decided to sit in two chairs with one butt}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.75,0:09:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,World lost its color completely.{/Everything became tasteless to me./Everything in the whole world became fade.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.36,0:09:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned the hard way that anyone is powerless \Nwhen facing a fate of death like that of Munakata.{had me scratching my head: you see, Lit is "In front of/Before Munakata's death fate, nobody is powerless - that was a reminder to me" but that makes little sense, other variant is that it's not "hiriki" but "higeki" which is tragedy and roughly translates into "Nothing is tragedy compared to Munakata's death" but that is a bit too shoehorned and also sounds clumsy}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.88,0:09:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I wandered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.94,0:09:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Aimlessly.{/Swept away.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.72,0:10:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Until one day, with nothing left to lose, \Nthe flow brought me to Eihei Temple.{/Then, when my self-confidence ran out completely, I arrived to Eihei Temple.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.56,0:10:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was as though my soul is screaming{/crying}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.75,0:10:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And aside from that, \NI had no other way forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.76,0:10:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That was exactly my season of wailing{/lamenting}.{I'm not sure if he means "the time I was supposed to be wailing" or "I was actually wailing" or just abstract "the time of wailing" so I sticked with the latter cus it sounds kul}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.36,0:10:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Till then,{he never said this part, but I added it for consistency} I didn't have a slightest idea \Nwhat this life is actually all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.24,0:10:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But with this experience, \Nthe understanding shook me to the bone.{/I acquired a first-hand impression./I came to feeling it in my marrow.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.95,0:10:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In that wailing I found \Na piece of mind and the pith{he is using variations of word "marrow" so often I'm starting to think it's a wicked reference all along} of life!{this is utterly stupid but I take pride in this line}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.39,0:10:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The young lady's bereavement{/has lost someone dear and} \Nis just entering her wailing season now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.90,0:10:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,By trying to run away from sorrow and anguish, \Nshe dooms herself to spending this way the rest of her life.{/to staying forever in this present without ever moving on.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.67,0:10:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If she doesn't confront this wailing head-on right away, \Nshe'll never be able to move on to{/live} a new life!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.99,0:10:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It must really be so. Running away {from this }is as good \Nas losing yourself.{/means losing.} I don't want such to happen to Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,While this man Katsura Daigo \Nmay actually be the straw for Hiromi to clutch at.{/may be able to relieve Hiromi.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.65,0:10:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. \NWe trust you to take care of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.82,0:11:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How come I suddenly have to go to the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.83,0:11:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You need this to break free from{/cast off the shackles of/be cleaned of} the{/this} anguish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.62,0:11:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Katsura has been the most earnest{/genial/entreating} \Nabout relieving your soul...{/is a splendid person, who reassured us you'll be fine with him.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.15,0:11:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He will never become what Coach was to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.70,0:11:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.67,0:11:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I only have one Coach - Coach Munakata!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.20,0:11:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi? Your friends are here to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.68,0:11:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.37,0:11:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you come out \Nto meet Maki, Ryuzaki and Todo?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.80,0:12:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.06,0:12:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{I'm sorry }You came through all the trouble \Nof coming{ here together} to pick her up...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.52,0:12:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to apologize.{/There was nothing you could do.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.98,0:12:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, if only there was anything I could do.{/I'm so sorry.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhm, Mrs. Oka...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.32,0:12:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mind if I have \Na little talk with Ms. Oka?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.99,0:12:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, Todo here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.67,0:12:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't feel like it, \Nyou don't have to answer.{/Lit: If you don't want to answer then I'm fine with leaving unaswered.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.46,0:12:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But please let me tell you just a few words.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.90,0:12:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Both me and Ozaki, as well as Chiba \Nhave always been looking closely after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.26,0:12:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why, whatever calamity you're going through, \Nwhatever anguish, everyone else is going through it as well.{/Therefore, however desperate times you're having now, however painful, everyone can understand/feel it very well.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.48,0:12:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,One way or another, today we're leaving at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.23,0:12:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But please don't forget -
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.69,0:13:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone is waiting for you{ to join us again}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.93,0:13:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to figure if there's anything else we can do for you, \Neveryone is waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.71,0:13:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Hiromi answer anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.84,0:13:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.83,0:13:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,She has been like this all along \Nsince we're back from the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.83,0:13:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyhow, I'll come again tomorrow. \NIf not tomorrow, then the day after.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.74,0:13:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.51,0:13:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.18,0:13:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come to the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.18,0:13:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I can go wherever, \Nwon't change a thing.{/Wherever I go, it's all the same [to me].}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.17,0:14:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you again for waiting. \NHiromi's belongings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.16,0:14:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Give my warmest gratitude to Katsura.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.45,0:14:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.35,0:14:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.10,0:14:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ma'am, we're off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.49,0:14:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you two to escort Hiromi to this temple.{/to accompany Hiromi to this temple./to bring ... to this temple with your hands.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.86,0:14:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring Oka?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.99,0:14:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Her parents are at risk of caving in to the pressure{/pain}{ if I ask that of them}.{/Asking that of her parents might just turn out too much for them.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.35,0:14:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If Oka bristles against{/resists the idea of} coming here, \Nwhat do you sanction{/advice} us to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.67,0:14:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If need be, bring her by the scruff{ of her neck}.{/Then I trust you to change her mind.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.98,0:15:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.86,0:15:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.61,0:15:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I take her in my custody now. \NThe rest of you go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.88,0:15:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.31,0:16:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.27,0:16:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.84,0:16:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop this at once! \NWhat's gotten into you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.51,0:16:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.69,0:16:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi can die!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.76,0:16:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Her body is tempered by training{guess, can't hear that first word}! \NIt can withstand much more than this{/It won't crumble under something as trivial}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.52,0:16:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.38,0:16:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki, Aikawa, \Nwe decided to entrust her to Katsura.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.78,0:16:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.30,0:16:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, bit by bit, \Nyou're regaining your humanity.{/you're already a bit more alive than before.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.62,0:16:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.52,0:17:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.63,0:18:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not time to sleep.{/I didn't dismiss you.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.79,0:18:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.78,0:18:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.39,0:18:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, nothing is unbearable in this life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.40,0:18:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\clip(85.868,409.143,564.437,460.571)\t(2000,3200,\clip(548.408,409.143,577.03,456))}Not even things like sorrow or anguish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.42,0:18:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.99,0:18:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't you start dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.29,0:18:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.61,0:18:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.88,0:18:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then neither do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.50,0:19:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mulish and dogged. Also selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.96,0:19:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She inherited your every downside,{/adopted your every bad habit,} Munakata!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.08,0:19:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.30,0:19:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder where can she be now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.25,0:19:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Maki, I'd prefer to return \Nwithout meeting Hiromi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.15,0:19:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Just knowing where she is would be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.18,0:20:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, such was Mr. Katsura's request.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.67,0:20:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a moment then!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.79,0:20:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, she is Zen meditating in that building.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.85,0:20:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure you want to come home \Nafter just that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.60,0:20:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We have already entrusted \NHiromi to Mr. Katsura.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.10,0:20:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi, don't give up, okay?\NI'll come visit you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.34,0:20:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask just one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.25,0:20:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what am I supposed to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.91,0:20:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem like I can die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.03,0:20:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the same time, \NI can't go on living like this either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.88,0:21:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you come here \Nhoping to find an answer to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.92,0:21:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think of that.{/Maybe I did./I don't know.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.06,0:21:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Five years ago, while Jin was still alive, I first experienced the sorrow of parting. The anguish, the heartbreak.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.86,0:21:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,From 16 till 22, we fought in a pair, or chased the same yellow ball, with net squeezed somewhere in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.04,0:21:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And envisioned us spending the next 5 years \Nthe exact same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.44,0:21:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,First death, then hope.\N I'm talking about you, Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.94,0:23:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Aikawa Maki here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.54,0:23:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems Mr. Katsura \Ndecided it's for the next step.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.19,0:23:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants Hiromi to inherit Coach Munakata's racket. \NHe's very insistent about her taking it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.21,0:23:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But can't you see? \NHiromi is still nowhere near sorting her feelings out!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.28,0:23:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too brutal, Mr. Katsura!\NShe is not yet ready to accept it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.50,0:23:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, \NMidorikawa gets into a terrible accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.60,0:24:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Next episode: Munakata Jin's Racket
